<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>CHDV&#160;23249.  Animal Behavior.  100 Units.</strong></p><p class="courseblockdesc">
This course introduces the mechanism, ecology, and evolution of behavior, primarily in nonhuman species, at the individual and group level. Topics include the genetic basis of behavior, developmental pathways, communication, physiology and behavior, foraging behavior, kin selection, mating systems and sexual selection, and the ecological and social context of behavior. A major emphasis is placed on understanding and evaluating scientific studies and their field and lab techniques.</p><p class="courseblockdetail">
