<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>CHDV&#160;25900.  Developmental Psychology.  100 Units.</strong></p><p class="courseblockdesc">
This is an introductory course in developmental psychology, with a focus on cognitive and social development in infancy through early childhood. Example topics include children's early thinking about number, morality, and social relationships, as well as how early environments inform children's social and cognitive development. Where appropriate, we make links to both philosophical inquiries into the nature of the human mind, and to practical inquiries concerning education and public policy.</p><p class="courseblockdetail">
